# YOLO Mode Guardrails

Even when running in YOLO mode (auto-approve commands), you MUST print a clear warning before executing any of these destructive operations:

## Always Warn Before
- `rm -rf` or `rm -r` on directories
- `git push --force` or `git push -f`
- `git reset --hard`
- `DROP TABLE`, `DROP DATABASE`
- `DELETE FROM` without WHERE clause
- `TRUNCATE TABLE`
- Database migrations without rollback scripts

## Safe to Auto-Run
- `npm run lint`, `npm run test`, `npm run build`
- `git status`, `git diff`, `git log`
- `npx tsc --noEmit` (type checking)
- Dev server start/stop

## Warning Format
```
DESTRUCTIVE: [command]
This will [consequence]. Proceed? (y/n)
```
